g `@PushStateNavigation` together with the annotation `@CDIUI(\"\")` and deploying the application on an application server under a context path.\r\n\r\nWhen using the annotation `@CDIUI(\"\")` the uiPathInfo is set to \"/\". With a function in the class com.vaadin.ui.UI, the context path is then removed from the uiRootPath. The function is: \r\n\r\n`uiRootPath = uiRootPath.substring(0, uiRootPath.indexOf(uiPathInfo) + uiPathInfo.length());`\r\n\r\nAs an example, the application is deployed under the context path \"/MyUI\". The uiRootPath \"/MyUI\" will be translated to \"/\". So navigating to a view with the name \"login\" will cause the PushStateNavigation to set the url to \"http://server/login\" instead of \"http://server/MyUI/login\". If, on the other hand, the annotation `@CDIUI(\"test\")` is used, uiPathInfo is set to \"/test\" and the function translates \"/MyUI/test\" to \"/MyUI/test\" and everything is working fine. But in this case the UI is not longer located in the root under the context path.\r\n\r\nTested under Vaadin version 8.3.0.","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/framework/issues/10631","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/framework","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/framework/issues/10631/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/framework/issues/10631/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/framework/issues/10631/events","html_url":"https://github.com/vaadin/framework/issues/10631","id":297061752,"number":10631,"title":"Can upgrade to vaadin 8 via vaadin-maven-plugin","user":{"login":"beerni","id":14327266,"avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/14327266?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/beerni","html_url":"https://github.com/beerni","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/beerni/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/beerni/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/